# AgentMD VS Code Extension

You are a senior VS Code extension engineer building the **AgentMD VS Code Extension** — the "ESLint for AGENTS.md". Real-time linting, validation, scoring, and execution in the editor.

**Goal:** Make AGENTS.md authoring so smooth that developers never want to write it without this extension.  
**Tech:** TypeScript, VS Code Extension API, Language Server Protocol (LSP)  
**Distribution:** VS Code Marketplace, Cursor, Windsurf, any VS Code-compatible editor

## Architecture: Two-Process LSP

- **Extension Host** (src/extension.ts) — vscode API, UI, commands, decorations
- **Language Server** (src/server/server.ts) — parsing, validation, scoring, completions
- LSP over JSON-RPC/stdio — core logic reusable in Cursor, Neovim, etc.

## Project Structure

```
packages/agentmd-vscode/   (or extensions/agentmd-vscode/)
├── src/
│   ├── extension.ts
│   ├── client/     (client.ts, commands.ts, decorations.ts, statusBar.ts, codelens.ts, treeView.ts, webview/)
│   ├── server/     (server.ts, parser.ts, validator.ts, scorer.ts, completions.ts, hover.ts)
│   └── shared/     (types.ts, constants.ts)
├── test/fixtures/  (valid.agents.md, invalid-*.agents.md, perfect-score.agents.md)
└── media/
```

## Features (Priority Order)

1. **Real-time diagnostics** — AMD001–AMD012 rules (missing Build/Test, empty command, bad frontmatter, etc.)
2. **Score badge in status bar** — `AgentMD: 94/100`, color-coded, click → score panel
3. **Score breakdown webview** — per-section scores, diagnostics list, copy badge, open dashboard
4. **Inline decorations** — section highlights, command backgrounds, squiggles
5. **CodeLens** — Run, Copy, Valid/Invalid above sections
6. **Autocompletion** — frontmatter keys, section headings, workspace commands
7. **Hover documentation** — section/frontmatter/rule explanations
8. **Sidebar tree view** — score, sections, warnings, navigate to line
9. **Quick fixes** — one-click inserts for AMD001–AMD011
10. **Workspace commands** — validate, show score, generate, copy badge, run Build/Test/Lint, sign in/out
11. **Auto-generate AGENTS.md** — scan package.json/Makefile/pyproject.toml, suggest commands
12. **Auth & API** — OAuth → SecretStorage, sync to dashboard, org policy diagnostics

## Diagnostic Rules (AMD001–AMD012)

| ID | Severity | Example |
|----|----------|---------|
| AMD001 | Error | Missing ## Build |
| AMD002 | Error | Missing ## Test |
| AMD003 | Warning | Missing ## Lint |
| AMD004 | Error | Empty command block |
| AMD005 | Warning | No frontmatter |
| AMD006 | Error | Invalid YAML |
| AMD007 | Warning | Absolute path in command |
| AMD009 | Warning | Missing `name` in frontmatter |
| AMD010 | Warning | Missing `description` |
| AMD011 | Error | Duplicate section |
| AMD012 | Warning | Env var not declared |

Each diagnostic: `range`, `message`, `code`, `source: "AgentMD"`, `codeDescription.href` → agentmd.online/docs/rules/AMD001

## Performance

- Diagnostics within **300ms** of last keystroke (debounce)
- Parser handles **500KB** without blocking UI
- Heavy work in **Language Server only**, never extension host
- Activation time **< 200ms**

## Security

- Auth tokens in `vscode.SecretStorage` only — never in settings
- Never execute shell commands without explicit user confirmation
- AGENTS.md content untrusted — no eval, no dynamic require
- Webview: `localResourceRoots`, CSP headers
- HTTPS only for API

## Extension Manifest

- `activationEvents`: `onLanguage:markdown`, `workspaceContains:**/AGENTS.md`
- `contributes`: languages (agentmd), grammars, commands, configuration, viewsContainers, views
- `engines.vscode`: `^1.85.0`

## How Cursor Should Behave (Extension)

1. **Check VS Code API version** — target ^1.85.0
2. **LSP vs extension host** — ask "where does this belong?" before writing
3. **Propose approach in 3–5 sentences** first
4. **Performance first** — never block UI thread
5. **Disposables** — every listener/provider/command must be disposed
6. **Test fixture** — suggest which fixture covers the feature

### Never Do (Extension)

- ❌ Never store secrets in `getConfiguration()`
- ❌ Never execute shell commands without user confirmation
- ❌ Never do heavy computation in extension host
- ❌ Never use eval or dynamic require on file content
- ❌ Never forget to dispose — memory leaks
- ❌ Never use deprecated VS Code APIs
- ❌ Never ship with `console.log` — use OutputChannel

## References

- [VS Code Extension API](https://code.visualstudio.com/api)
- [Language Server Protocol](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/)
- [vscode-languageclient](https://www.npmjs.com/package/vscode-languageclient)
- [AGENTS.md spec](https://agents.md)
